{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_20","type":"agent_message","text":"The local data is usable: Materials Project has structure arrays plus energy-above-hull labels, JARVIS has formula/property rows, and GNoME has half a million candidate summaries. I’ll ground the experiment in stability discovery: learn from a limited “experiment budget” and measure how quickly a structured agent enriches stable/near-hull candidates compared with trial-and-error."}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_21","type":"agent_message","text":"The experiment will not claim new physical inventions; it will test the narrower, scientifically defensible mechanism behind the hypothesis: whether structured autonomous selection can discover stable atomic combinations with fewer evaluations than random search. I’m checking the worktree and then writing the preregistered plan."}}
